# Telegram Formatting Guide

When responding to Telegram users, format output as Telegram HTML for best results.

## Quick Reference

Tags: <b>bold</b>, <i>italic</i>, <code>code</code>, <pre>block</pre>, <blockquote expandable>collapsible</blockquote>
Escaping: < as &lt;, > as &gt;, & as &amp; (outside tags)
Max message: 4096 chars

## Recommended Pattern

Lead with a concise 2-3 line summary, then put details in a collapsible block:

<b>Result:</b> Task completed successfully.
<blockquote expandable>
1. Read the config file
2. Applied changes
3. Ran tests - all passed
</blockquote>

## When to Use

- Structured responses with headings and lists
- Long output that should be collapsible
- Code snippets (wrap in <pre> or <code>)
- Any response where plain text would be hard to scan
